Introduction:
=============
  This testbench verifies a simple UART receiver
  Fixed baud rate at 115200
  Clock frequency is 10Mhz
  1 start bit
  8 data bits (LSB first)
  1 stop bit
  no parity
  Upon completing the transfer, the DUT outputs the 8-bit data with 
  valid signal asserted for one clock

Data Check
==============
1. Create UART transaction class that contains the random 8-bit data
2. UART driver receives UART packet, then add start and stop bits  and sends the data serially
3. UART driver also sends the packet to ap port (reference)
4. UART monitor checks for the stop bit
5. UART monitor detects o_valid and captures o_data (actual)
6. The scoreboard performs the comparison of reference and actual data

